3 SECTION 4. AMENDATORY 74 O.S. 2021, Section 85.42, as
4 amended by Section 9, Chapter 336, O.S.L. 2025 (74 O.S. Supp. 2025,
5 Section 85.42), is amended to read as follows:
6 Section 85.42. A. 1. Except as otherwise provided for in this
7 section or other applicable law, any agency, whether or not such
8 agency is subject to the Oklahoma Central Purchasing Act, shall be
9 prohibited from entering into a sole-source contract or agreement or
10 a contract or agreement for professional services with or for the
11 services of any person who has terminated employment with or who has
12 been terminated by that agency for one (1) year after the
13 termination date of the employee from the agency. Any contract or
14 agreement entered into in violation of this subsection shall be
15 void. Any person found to have violated this subsection shall be
16 prohibited from entering into any state contract for a period of
17 five (5) years from the date of the execution of the contract or
18 agreement. The provisions of this subsection shall not prohibit an
19 agency from hiring or rehiring such person as a state employee.
20 2. Any chief administrative officer of an agency, whether or
21 not such agency is subject to the Oklahoma Central Purchasing Act,
22 shall not enter into any contract for nonprofessional or
23 professional services for the purpose of or which would result in
24
Req. No. 16845 Page 27

1 the circumvention of the full-time-equivalent employee limitation
2 established by law for such agency.
